25/08/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski arrived Monday (25 August) for a two-day visit at the invitation of his Bulgarian counterpart, Georgi Parvanov.
They will discuss opportunities to enhance bilateral ties, especially in the fields of tourism and trade.
The two presidents are also to discuss possible co-operation in terms of EU and NATO membership, as well as the participation of a Bulgarian peacekeeping unit in Karbala, Iraq as part of the Polish-led multinational division.
Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, meanwhile, left for Baghdad on Sunday to discuss his country's participation in the reconstruction effort.
He and a delegation representing the business community met with an aide to L Paul Bremer, the US civilian administrator of Iraq.
Passy will also visit the Bulgarian Embassy in Baghdad to assess damage there.
(BTA, Trud, 24 Chassa, Dnevnik, Sega - 25/08/03;
AFP, Trud, 24 Chassa, BTA, BNT - 24/08/03)
